          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is a healthy BMI for someone over 50?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "The standard WHO range of 18.5–24.9 applies to adults over 50, but some evidence suggests BMI 22–27 may be associated with better health outcomes in older adults. This is partly because low BMI after 50 can indicate muscle loss (sarcopenia) rather than genuine leanness, which carries its own health risks."
